    "body": "\n## Problem\n\nDuring the MLA decode phase on ROCm with the Aiter backend, a\nvectorized_elementwise GPU kernel is launched to zero-fill the output tensor\nbefore the MLA kernel overwrites it entirely. This adds unnecessary kernel\nlaunch latency on the critical decode path.\n\n## Root\n\nIn `rocm_aiter_mla.py`, the output tensor `o` is allocated with `torch.zeros`:\n\n```python\no = torch.zeros(\n    B,\n    self.num_heads,\n    self.kv_lora_rank,\n    dtype=attn_metadata.decode.attn_out_dtype,\n    device=q.device,\n)\n```\n\n`torch.zeros` launches a `vectorized_elementwise` fill kernel on the GPU.\nHowever, the Aiter MLA kernel pipeline (`mla_decode_fwd`) unconditionally\noverwrites every element of `o` before it is read:\n\n- When `num_kv_splits > 1`: the Stage 2 Triton reduction kernel stores\n  `acc / e_sum` to every valid position in `O`.\n- When `num_kv_splits == 1` and Stage 2 runs: the `FINAL_OUT` path copies from\n  the intermediate buffer to `O`.\n- When `num_kv_splits == 1` with early return: either `logits` aliases `o`\n  (Stage 1 writes through the alias) or the ASM kernel writes to `ptr_RP`\n  directly.\n\nThe zero-initialization is therefore redundant.\n\n\n## Fix\n\nReplace `torch.zeros` with `torch.empty`, which only allocates memory without launching\nany GPU kernel.\n\nNote that the Aiter sparse MLA backend (`rocm_aiter_mla_sparse.py`) already\nuses `torch.empty` for its output tensor. This change makes the dense backend\nconsistent.\n\n## Test Result\n\n- Eliminates one `vectorized_elementwise` GPU kernel launch per decode step\n  per layer.\n- No effect on other MLA backends (Triton, FlashAttn, FlashMLA, FlashInfer,\n  CUTLASS) -- each backend allocates its own output tensor independently.\n\nAccuracy test with Kimi-K2-Thinking.\n\nWith torch.zeros()\n\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9030|±  |0.0082|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.8931|±  |0.0085|\n\nWith torch.empty()\n\n|Tasks|Version|     Filter     |n-shot|  Metric   |   |Value |   |Stderr|\n|-----|------:|----------------|-----:|-----------|---|-----:|---|-----:|\n|gsm8k|      3|flexible-extract|     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9227|±  |0.0074|\n|     |       |strict-match    |     5|exact_match|↑  |0.9105|±  |0.0079|",
